  "text": "G L U T A M I N E Glutamine is a neutral amino acid which is obtained directly from the diet or indirectly by conversion from a-ketoglutarate or transamination of other amino acids. Glutamine was originally classified as non-essential but is now considered to be conditionally essential in many pathological states [CITATION_1] ).",
